President Donald J. Trump recently hosted a working dinner in New York with several Latin American leaders, including President Michel Temer of Brazil, President Juan Manuel Santos of Colombia, President Juan Carlos Varela of Panama, and Vice President Gabriela Michetti of Argentina. During the dinner, the leaders discussed the importance of restoring democracy to Venezuela and expressed their support for the Venezuelan people. They also reaffirmed the principles of the Lima Declaration and agreed to continue working together to resolve the Venezuelan crisis. Additionally, the leaders discussed ways to improve security in the Western Hemisphere, promote prosperity, and uphold democracy and the rule of law. Foreign ministers from the region will meet this week to further discuss these ideas.